abstract: >
  DFFP4LHM provides R scripts for calculating Land Use Heterogeneity (LHM) 
  metrics while explicitly considering Data-Fitness-for-Purpose (DFFP) 
  principles. The package enables researchers in agrosystems science to 
  quantify landscape heterogeneity while assessing whether spatial data 
  quality is adequate for the intended analytical purpose. The tools support 
  FAIR data practices by incorporating data quality and fitness-for-use 
  assessments into spatial heterogeneity analysis workflows.
